          <h2 class="font-heading text-[#FF5E15] text-2xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Common Equipment Issues in Nashville</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Broadway & Downtown: Motor Burnout</h3>
              <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">Nashville's Lower Broadway restaurants run exhaust systems 16-20 hours a day. Motors burn out faster in high-volume, grease-heavy environments. Direct-drive upblast fans with sealed motors last longer, but even they need replacement every 3-5 years under these conditions. If your motor is screaming, vibrating, or tripping breakers — <a href="/repair/nashville-tn/" class="text-[#FF5E15] hover:underline">call for emergency repair</a> before it seizes and takes the fan wheel with it.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Hot Chicken Joints: Filter Saturation</h3>
              <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">Nashville hot chicken generates extreme grease loads. Standard cleaning schedules aren't enough — filters saturate faster, ductwork builds up quicker, and fire risk climbs. We supply extra filter sets so you can rotate while cleaning, and our <a href="/cleaning/nashville-tn/" class="text-[#FF5E15] hover:underline">hood cleaning crews</a> know exactly what hot chicken kitchens demand.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-heading text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2">The Gulch & Midtown: TPO Roof Damage</h3>
              <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">Newer Nashville construction uses white TPO roofing. Grease runoff from exhaust fans stains and degrades TPO membranes, voiding manufacturer warranties. Our <a href="/grease-containment/" class="text-[#FF5E15] hover:underline">rooftop grease containment systems</a> — boxes, trays, and absorbent pads — prevent grease from ever reaching your roof surface.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal-child">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-[#FF5E15] text-2xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Nashville Parts & Compliance</h2>
          <div class="space-y-5">
            <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">The <strong class="text-white">Metro Nashville Fire Marshal</strong> enforces NFPA 96 for all commercial kitchen exhaust systems. Inspectors check for hinge kits on upblast fans, fire-rated access panels on ductwork, proper grease containment, and clean filters. Every part we install meets or exceeds these standards.</p>
            <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]"><strong class="text-white">Metro Water Services (MWS)</strong> enforces Fats, Oils, and Grease (FOG) regulations. Grease leaving your property — whether through drains or rooftop runoff — can result in fines. Proper grease containment on your rooftop exhaust fans keeps you compliant on both fire and environmental codes.</p>
            <p class="text-[#D4D4D4]">Every part we install is documented with photos and service records for your compliance files. Learn more about <a href="/nfpa-code-96-standards/" class="text-[#FF5E15] hover:underline">NFPA 96 standards and what they mean for your kitchen</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
